The defendant Melissa A. Wenckebach was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Capture an Image of Nudity [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 942.09(2)(am)1.
  • Capture an Image of Nudity [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 942.09(2)(am)1.
  • Capture an Image of Nudity [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 942.09(2)(am)1.
  • Capture an Image of Nudity [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 942.09(2)(am)1.
  • Capture an Image of Nudity [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 942.09(2)(am)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

superMiscConds.notes:
Bond applied  -  Balance still to be collected.
If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  This applies to all counts and financial obligations.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.  
*  Pay supervision fees.  
Do not possess or consume alcoholic beverages and do not have alcoholic beverages within the residence.  Do not possess or consume controlled substances, except by prescription.  Submit voluntarily to random tests of blood, breath or urine.  Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by agent.  Counseling shall specifically include:  AODA Assessment and follow through with recommended treatment.  
*  Pay fine of $300  and court costs including all applicable surcharges.    
*  If unpaid financial obligations remain at discharge or revocation, civil judgment to be entered. 
*  DE is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay DNA surcharge and notice is given.   
May not have contact with minors, with the exception of her son or any biological child, or co-defendant without permission of the agent.  No contact with any victims.  No possession of electronic devices capable of accessing the internet without approval of the agent.  No possession of devices enabled to record visual images or auditory records without approval of the agent.  Participate in and follow recommendations of a mental health evaluation.  Register as a Sex Offender for 15 years from the conclusion of sentences.
